03:03.975 --> 03:07.686
Well, it's close to Italy,
and after London and New York ...

03:07.729 --> 03:09.605
... I was director at the Venice orchestra.

03:09.689 --> 03:11.857
- Of course!
- For twenty-four years.

03:12.233 --> 03:13.859
Silly of me!

03:14.569 --> 03:16.945
And are you still directing
or composing, Maestro?

03:17.363 --> 03:19.448
No. I'm retired.

03:21.743 --> 03:25.245
Maestro, as I indicated you
In my letter, I work ...

03:25.371 --> 03:27.998
... For the Entitlements and Events
Office at the Buckingham Palace.

03:28.249 --> 03:32.002
- You work for the Queen?
- In a sense, yes.

03:32.253 --> 03:34.713
Good. I find Monarchies
so endearing.

03:35.089 --> 03:37.758
If I may, Maestro ...

03:38.092 --> 03:40.886
Why exactly do You find
the monarchy endearing?

03:41.012 --> 03:43.263
Well, because it's so vulnerable.

03:43.765 --> 03:46.600
You eliminate one person ...

03:46.893 --> 03:48.852
... And all of a sudden ...

03:49.020 --> 03:51.480
... The whole world changes.

03:54.901 --> 03:57.027
Like in a marriage.

03:58.363 --> 04:02.991
Maestro, Her Majesty The Queen
would be honoured to confer ..

04:03.034 --> 04:05.410
