no talent again, you idiot.

18:35.489 --> 18:37.907
Now there is not the time for fermentation.
You talentless parasite!

18:38.117 --> 18:40.743
That's enough, you're really
getting on my nerves.

18:40.786 --> 18:42.662
We have to come up with an ending.

18:43.122 --> 18:45.414
And you waste your time
talking Philosophy and Big Ideas.

18:45.666 --> 18:47.500
He is on his deathbed ...

18:47.918 --> 18:49.669
He can barely talk ...

18:50.420 --> 18:52.421
He whispers to his wife:

18:53.048 --> 18:54.799
"Don't cry, honey."

18:55.134 --> 19:00.513
"You know, I've always found women
who weep frivolent and repulsive. "

19:00.556 --> 19:03.057
- Nice!
- That's a totally asinine idea.

19:03.392 --> 19:04.809
What else?

19:23.078 --> 19:24.954
You won't fool me!

19:25.831 --> 19:28.833
I know that you can't levitate.

20:13.879 --> 20:15.379
That's everything?

20:20.886 --> 20:23.137
Don't you need anything?

20:33.649 --> 20:36.150
- What do you need band-aids for?
- I don't.

20:36.401 --> 20:39.737
I'm doing it out of solidarity
with you.

20:40.781 --> 20:42.657
Ah, fuck you.

20:49.164 --> 20:50.998
You pay.

20:52.501 --> 20:54.418
Do you remember Gilda?

20:55.671 --> 20:58.130
- The film?
- No, Gilda Black.

20:58.173 --> 21:01.300
The girl that we were both
in love with.

21:01.635 --> 21:03.636
Gilda Black?

21:03.679 --> 21:07.014
What are you ...
Have to remind me up for?

21:07.182 --> 21:09.308
That was a hundred years ago.

21:10.435 --> 21:13.187
To me it seems like yesterday.

21:14.314 --> 21:18.651
I would have given twenty years of my life
to have slept with her.

21:18.694 --> 21:21.070
Well, that would've been
a pretty stupid thing.

21:21.154 --> 21:24.073
Guilda Black wasn't worth
twenty years of life.

21:24.157 --> 21:26.284
She wasn't worth a single day.

21:28.078 --> 21:29.787
How do you know?

21:30.956 --> 21:32.790
Did you sleep with her?

21:33.041 --> 21:35.084
What? What did you say?

21:35.335 --> 21:37.086
You heard me.

21:37.212 --> 21:39.547
Sixty years ago you swore
you never slept with her ...

21:39.589 --> 21:41.966
... out of respect of my love for her.

21:42.092 --> 21:44.593
Now you've changed your tune.

21:47.222 --> 21:48.848
Look...

21:49.099 --> 21:52.226
- I have something to confess.
- Fine, go ahead!

21:52.728 --> 21:54.437
The real tragedy ...

21:54.563 --> 21:57.481
And, believe me, it really is a tragedy ...

21:57.858 --> 22:01.861
Is that I can't even remember
if I slept with Gilda Black.

22:03.238 --> 22:05.948
- Are you serious?
- I swear.

22:09.578 --> 22:13.998
I'm wondering what happens
to your memory over time.

22:15.751 --> 22:18.627
I can't remember my family.

22:19.379 --> 22:21.005
I don't remember...

22:21.340 --> 22:24.133
Their faces or how they talked.

22:26.511 --> 22:30.264
Last night I was watching Lena
while she was asleep.

22:30.515 --> 22:33.642
And I was thinking about
all the thousands of little things ...

22:33.769 --> 22:37.271
... That I done for her as her father.

22:37.856 --> 22:42.651
And I done them deliberately
so that she would remember them ...

22:42.736 --> 22:44.904
... When she grows up.

22:45.030 --> 22:47.114
But in time ...

22:47.407 --> 22:49.909
... She won't remember a single thing.

22:53.747 --> 22:55.998
Tremendous effort, Mick,
you know.

22:58.377 --> 23:01.045
Tremendous efforts, Mick.

23:02.255 --> 23:04.131
With a modest result.

25:19.809 --> 25:23.312
They're going to talk tonight, mostly.

25:23.522 --> 25:27.191
I will bet you thirty Swiss francs ...

25:27.776 --> 25:30.152
... They don't say a word
the entire dinner.

25:30.195 --> 25:33.697
I'm so sure they are going to talk.

25:35.325 --> 25:37.785
- I'll raise you to fifty.
- Done.

25:45.085 --> 25:48.295
Including the last few days, err ...

25:48.338 --> 25:53.842
... You owe me 250 Swiss francs.

26:15.740 --> 26:17.866
Today?

26:18.201 --> 26:20.619
Not today. You?

26:23.957 --> 26:25.499
Nothing.

26:27.085 --> 26:29.753
Let's hope we take a piss tomorrow.

27:12.422 --> 27:13.797
That's great, Nick.

27:13.882 --> 27:16.550
I'm glad you liked
the second draft.

27:16.676 --> 27:18.510
Sure, we will work some more
on the ending.

27:18.553 --> 27:20.554
I'll talk to Brenda,
everything is all set.

27:21.181 --> 27:25.059
She can't wait. When is she ever going
to get a part like this at her age, come on!

27:25.310 --> 27:29.688
If it's okay with you, I'd like to start
scouting locations next month

27:29.814 --> 27:31.774
- Perfect. Bye!
- Yeah.

27:32.817 --> 27:34.943
What happened to you?

27:35.278 --> 27:38.072
You look like you've been to a funeral.

27:39.699 --> 27:41.450
Your son...

27:41.660 --> 27:44.328
- Has left my daughter.
- Fuck!

27:44.412 --> 27:47.581
- What are you talking about?
- They were boarding a plane to Polynesia.

27:47.707 --> 27:50.417
And right there, in the tunnel
he stops ...

27:50.460 --> 27:55.339
... And tells her that he's fallen
in love with another woman.

27:56.841 --> 28:00.344
Nothing like being in the tunnel
to make you feel you are in the tunnel.

28:00.428 --> 28:04.348
How fond! You're quite a magician
of metaphor.

28:04.474 --> 28:06.850
And he took this other woman
on vacation?

28:06.976 --> 28:10.187
At least he had the good taste
not to do so. At least

28:10.230 --> 28:11.730
And Lena?

28:11.856 --> 28:13.982
